<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>About Scottish Pantry Network</title>
    <!-- CSS and JavaScript links can be included here -->
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f7f7f7;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 1200px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 20px;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        .header {
            background-color: #67b0b7;
            color: #fff;
            padding: 20px;
            text-align: center;
            border-radius: 10px 10px 0 0;
        }

        .vision {
            background-color: #fff;
            color: #333;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 0 0 10px 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .vision h2 {
            color: #67b0b7;
        }

        .mission {
            margin-top: 40px;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            background-color: #f1f1f1;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .mission h3 {
            color: #67b0b7;
        }

        .values {
            margin-top: 40px;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            background-color: #fff;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .values h3 {
            color: #67b0b7;
        }

        .points {
            list-style-type: none;
            padding-left: 20px;
            margin: 0;
        }

        .points li {
            margin-bottom: 10px;
            font-size: 16px;
        }

        .points li:before {
            content: "•";
            color: #67b0b7;
            display: inline-block;
            width: 1em;
            margin-left: -1em;
        }

        .btn {
            display: inline-block;
            background-color: #67b0b7;
            color: #fff;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
        }


        .pantries {
            margin-top: 40px;
            display: flex;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            justify-content: space-around;
        }

        .pantry-card {
            width: 45%;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            background-color: #f1f1f1;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        @media screen and (max-width: 768px) {

            .mission,
            .values {
                padding: 10px;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="header">
            <h1>Scottish Pantry Network</h1>
        </div>
        <div class="vision">
            <h2>Our Vision</h2>
            <p>Our vision is to establish a sustainable network of pantries providing affordable food and wrap-around
                services. The pantry is a dignified approach empowering communities to help themselves. We will support
                upskilling the community through volunteering and employability opportunities, with the shop itself
                being utilized as a training facility.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mission">
            <h3>Our Mission</h3>
            <p>The Scottish Pantry Network will support the pantries by being the collective voice for change. We forge
                strong partnerships to support the development of the hub model, creating a tailored experience for
                local communities. The Network will provide ongoing support to the pantries through compliance,
                lobbying, and creating links with food suppliers.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="values">
            <h3>Our Values</h3>
            <ul class="points">
                <li><strong>Prevention of Poverty:</strong> Providing food security to those who need it most and are
                    disadvantaged due to unemployment, low income, lone parenthood, health, and social standing.</li>
                <li><strong>Advancement of Community Development:</strong> Acting on behalf of the Network of Pantries,
                    sourcing food to ensure there is enough in the supply chain, lobbying government, providing a
                    regulatory function, and sharing best practice across the Network.</li>
                <li><strong>Advancement of Environmental Protection:</strong> Reducing food waste locally and
                    nationally.</li>
                <li><strong>Advancement of Education:</strong> Increasing access to skills, training, and employment
                    prospects in relation to developing and running a local pantry.</li>
                <li><strong>Advancement of Health:</strong> Improving health outcomes – particularly around the
                    consumption of fresh fruit and vegetables, through social eating, improving emotional wellbeing and
                    social inclusion through Pantries acting as community hubs, and promoting access to nutritious meals
                    and increasing fruit and vegetable consumption.</li>
                <li><strong>Relief for Those in Need:</strong> Providing access to key support such as money advice,
                    credit unions, housing, health, employment, and skills.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <br>
         <h3 style="text-align:center;">Our Pantries</h3>
        <div class="pantries">
           
            <div class="pantry-card">
                {{#each pantries}}
                <h3 style="color: #67b0b7">{{pantryName}}</h3>
                <p><strong >Location:</strong> {{location}}, {{address}}, {{postcode}}</p>

                {{/each}}
            </div>


        </div>

        <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 20px;">
            <a href="/" class="btn">Back to Home</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>